Four generations of peas grown in orbit were no different from the terrestrial varieties.
Then came the breeding of insects in orbit, small fruit flies, drosophilas.
In 1979 quail eggs were sent to space to check how the embryo develops under weightless conditions.
The result is a normal chick.
But then the problems begin.
