Larry Hagman, whose role as predator oil magnate J.R. Ewing on the television series "Dallas" became a symbol of greed in the 1980s, has died.
He was 81 years old.
Hagman, who returned this year as J.R. in a new season of "Dallas," died Friday afternoon due to cancer complications, according to a family statement provided to The Associated Press by Warner Bros., the producing house of "Dallas."
